# cpass (C Password Generator)

A minimalist, high-performance password generator for Linux, written in C.
It leverages `/dev/urandom` directly to ensure cryptographic security without external dependencies.



## Installation

### From Source

*(`make` is required)*

```bash
git clone [https://github.com/CarvDev/cpass.git](https://github.com/CarvDev/cpass.git)
cd cpass
make
sudo make install

```

## Usage

Generate a standard 16-character password:

```bash
cpass

```

Generate a 32-character password:

```bash
cpass 32

```